fields.title: Cat fact 57
fields.message: A cat rubs against people to mark its territory.

fields.title: Cat Fact 63
fields.message: Most cats don’t like water because their coats do not insulate them well enough.

fields.title: Cat Fact 26
fields.message: Cats make more than 100 different sounds whereas dogs make around 10.

fields.title: Cat Fact 13
fields.message: The world’s largest cat measured 48.5 inches long.

fields.title: Cat Fact 17
fields.message: Adult cats only meow to communicate with humans.

fields.title: Cat Fact 77
fields.message: The largest litter of kittens produced 19 kittens.

fields.title: Cat Fact 29
fields.message: A cat’s cerebral cortex (the part of the brain in charge of cognitive information processing) has 300 million neurons, compared with a dog’s 160 million.

fields.title: Cat Fact 46
fields.message: Cats can change their meow to manipulate a human. They often imitate a human baby when they need food, for example.

fields.title: Cat Fact 48
fields.message: Cats only sweat through their foot pads.
